original: Holmberg, Folke Henning Gustaf, rådman, notarius publicus, Västervik, f. 31/5/88 i Malmö av grosshandl. Magnus H. o. Augusta Holmberg. G. 1. 17 m. Martha Lindahl; 2. 24 m. Greta Margit Rudin. Barn: Bengt f. 18, Gerd 21, Sven 28, Kerstin 37. -Stud:ex. i Lund 08, jur. kand. 13. Kapt. i L 4 res. 45. E. o. not. i hovr. över Skåne o. Blek. 13, tf. domhav. 14-17, stadsfogde i Västervik 18, sekr. i hamndirekt. 20, förste rådm. sed. .21, tillika not. publ. Kamr. i Kalmar 1. norra landsting 24, sekr. sed. 41, tillsyn :m’an v. kronohäktet i Väsitervik fr. 28 t. tjänstens indragn. RVO 37.
translated: Holmberg, Folke Henning Gustaf, councilor, notary public, of Västervik, born on May 31, 1888 in Malmö to businessman Magnus H. and Augusta Holmberg. Married twice, first for 17 months to Martha Lindahl and then for 24 months to Greta Margit Rudin. Children: Bengt (born) in 1918, Gerd in 1921, Sven in 1928, and Kerstin in 1937. Studied at Lund University, graduated with a law degree in 1913. Captain in L 4 reserve in 1945. Appointed as a deputy notary in the Court of Appeal for Skåne and Blekinge in 1913, acting judge from 1914-1917, then appointed as city bailiff in Västervik in 1918, secretary in the port authority in 1920, appointed as the first councilor since 1921, also serving as a notary public. Became a member of the Chamber of Commerce in Kalmar, County Council in northern landsting in 1924, secretary since 1941, with oversight of the Kronohäktet in Västervik since 1928 until the end of service. Was awarded the Royal Order of Vasa in 1937.
